      "label": "Russian domains & IPs",
      "description": "Route Russian TLDs (.ru/.su/IDN), service CDNs (Yandex/VK/Avito/2GIS/banks/etc) and Russian IP ranges directly. Also brings the 'ru VPN 🇷🇺' selector (RU proxies only) and adds an !RU filter to proxy-out/auto-proxy-out so Russian traffic doesn't accidentally exit through a Russian proxy when the main proxy group is used.",
      "vars": [
        {
          "name": "out",
          "type": "outbound",
          "default": "direct-out",
          "title": "Outbound",
          "tooltip": "Where to route traffic for Russian domains and IPs."
